        walkthrough = '1. Examine the ??? in Arrapago Reef at (H-10) Map 1 for a cutscene.\n   - A Lamian Fang Key is required to reach this point.\n   - Lamian Fang Keys drop from Lamiae and Draugers in the area.\n   - You can also receive a Lamian Fang Key from a ??? spot in Caedarva Mire (I-7) Map 1 (southern part of the block).  You can obtain a new key from there once every game day.\n2. You no longer have to be on Corsair for the rest of this quest.\n3. You are asked to fish up a Hydrogauge.\n   - The item you need must be fished up in Al Zahbi, Aht Urhgan Whitegate, Nashmau, or the Ferry - Nashmau/Al Zahbi.\n   - You may use any rod and bait\n   - The fishing message you will receive is the standard item message, "You feel something pulling at your line".\n     - It is suggested to use any rod for large fish (ie: S.H. Fishing Rod)  and Insect Balls in Aht Urhgan Whitegate as this has a limited number of fish that may interfere with your fishing attempts.\n4. Once you\'ve fished up a Hydrogauge, trade it to Leleroon, Nashmau (G-7).\n5. Head to (G-8) in Wajaom Woodlands and trade the Hydrogauge to the Leypoint.\n   - This can be reached quickly using an Olduum Ring\n   - The Survival Guide is also fairly close-by.\n6. Wait one minute, then examine the Leypoint again.\n7. Return to the ??? in Arrapago Reef  at (H-10) Map 1 for your reward.',
